parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The ignition switch starts to come apart
causing the vehicle not to start; the vehicle catches fire; the ignition switch is stuck; the vehicle overheats and smokes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off without warning, resulting in loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine cuts off completely; the vehicle stalls without warning; the vehicle shuts off while driving; the ignition module overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The alternator connectors catch on fire; the alternator causes a fire; the vehicle catches fire while parked or driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire; electrical wiring harness overheats and melts; smoke comes from under the dash; the vehicle's computer system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracks and leaks in the fuel tank can cause gasoline to spill onto the ground, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor
fuel leaks from the top of the tank
fuel spills onto the ground when filling up
fuel tank cracks
fuel fumes inside the vehicle
and difficulty filling up the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to honor the recall can lead to continued use of a defective fuel tank, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealership refusal to repair or replace the fuel tank
citing warranty expiration or non-eligibility for the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or inadequate repair can lead to continued use of a defective fuel tank, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealership delay in repairing or replacing the fuel tank
incomplete repair
or failure to diagnose the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt buckle can lead to the belt not latching or unlatching, compromising the safety of the occupant in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch or unlatch
the buckle releases from the locking mechanism
the buckle does not click or lock
the buckle breaks or cracks
the seat belt does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat belt retractor can cause the belt to not lock in place, compromising the safety of the occupant in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails to lock
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate seat belt anchorage can cause the seat belt to detach or not function properly, compromising the safety of the occupant in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt anchor bolt cracks
the seat belt detaches from the anchor
the seat belt is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An incompatible child safety seat can cause the seat to wobble or not function properly, compromising the safety of the child in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The child safety seat wobbles
the seat belt does not properly secure the child safety seat.
